<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 22 at 2:47AM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Union County
through 330 AM CDT...
At 246 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
El Dorado, moving east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Smackover, Norphlet, Calion, Urbana, Lawson, Wesson,
Newell, New London, Pigeon Hill, Hillsboro, Kenova and Catesville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 AM CDT for south central
Arkansas.</instruction>
